jp.ac.toyota_ti.coin.wipefinder.server.utils

Class ResourceProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • jp.ac.toyota_ti.coin.wipefinder.server.utils.ResourceProvider

  • public class ResourceProvider
extends java.lang.Object
    A convenient class to store and retrieve all resources needed like DB, Properties Files, SockRoom... Usage: By default the resource provider can gives access to the Database Interface, the default properties File and the Taxonomy provider. Each resource has to be added to the provider, ex: DBInterfacer dbi = new DBInterfacer((String)pp.getValue("annotation.DB.Name"), (String)pp.getValue("annotation.DB.Host"), (String)pp.getValue("annotation.DB.User"), (String)pp.getValue("annotation.DB.PW")); Provider.addResource(RP_PROVIDED_RESOURCES.ANNOTATION_DBI, dbi); Or WikipediaCategorizer Categorizer = new JWPLWikipediaCategorizer(); Provider.addResource("WipeFinderCategorizer", Categorizer); Then the resources can be accessed as follow: (String)ResourceProvider.getPropertiesProvider(RP_PROVIDED_RESOURCES.PROPERTIES_PROVIDER).getValue("mysqlDBName"); Or (WikipediaCategorizer)ResourceProvider.getPropertiesProvider("WipeFinderCategorizer");
    Author:
    dw
